	h3
		b Cobb Douglas
	p $$U=f(x,y)$$
	p $$U=x^\alpha y^\beta $$
	p $$MU_x=\alpha x^{\alpha -1}y^\beta $$
	p $$MU_x=\alpha \frac{y^\beta }{x^{1- \alpha }}$$
	p $$MU_y=\beta \frac{x^\alpha}{y^{1- \beta }}$$
	p So:
	p $$\frac{MU_x}{MU_y}=\frac{\alpha \frac{y^\beta }{x^{1- \alpha }} }{\beta \frac{x^\alpha}{y^{1- \beta }}}$$
	p $$\frac{MU_x}{MU_y}=\frac{\alpha }{\beta }\frac{y}{x}$$
	p And we know:
	p $$\frac{MU_x}{MU_y}=\frac{p_x}{p_y}$$
	p So:
	$$\frac{\alpha }{\beta }\frac{y}{x}=\frac{p_x}{p_y}$$
	
